Newcastle disease, Bulgaria
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 10 Feb 2016 from Dr Damyan Iliev, Chief Veterinary Officer & Deputy Executive Director, Bulgarian Food Safety Agency, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Sofia, Bulgaria

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 2 Feb 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 5 Feb 2016
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 24 Jan 2013
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Paramyxovirus virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Nenkovo, Kardzali [Kurdzhali]
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Feb 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 301 / 61 / 61 / 240 / 0
Affected population: Backyard poultry
Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 20.27 / 20.27 / 100 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Source of the outbreak (s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Control measures: movement control inside the country; screening; vaccination in response to the outbreak (s); disinfection/disinfestations; traceability; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; stamping out; official destruction of animal products; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
National reference laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Birds / pathogen isolation by egg inoculation / 9 Feb 2016 / Positive
Birds / real-time PCR / 5 Feb 2016 / Positive

Future reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.

